                     GEOGRAPHIC RESTRICTIONS NOTICE

Residents of any countries, states, or territories that require age
verification for operating systems are NOT authorized to use FemDeb OS.

This restriction currently applies to the following jurisdictions:

  • Brazil — effective March 17, 2026

This restriction will additionally apply to the following jurisdictions
if their currently proposed legislation is enacted into law:

  • Colorado
  • Illinois
  • New York

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  NOTE: California — A restriction was previously anticipated effective
  January 1, 2027. This entry will be updated as the legal status of
  California's legislation is clarified.
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The FemDeb project urges all affected users to contact their elected
representatives and advocate for the repeal or replacement of these laws.
Age verification mandates for general-purpose software represent a
significant threat to digital privacy, free expression, and open-source
development. Your voice matters.

This list is subject to change as legislation is enacted, amended, or
repealed. Users are responsible for ensuring their use of FemDeb OS
complies with the laws of their jurisdiction.

